article.story: GREENVILLE, S.C. -- — JP Pegues scored 21 points as Furman beat Presbyterian 76-61 on Tuesday night. Pegues shot 8 for 12 (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 3 of 3 from the free throw line for the Paladins (6-6). Garrett Hien scored 19 points while going 8 of 12 and 2 of 5 from the free throw line, and added 11 rebounds and five assists. Pjay Smith Jr. was 3 of 13 shooting (2 for 10 from 3-point range) to finish with eight points. Marquis Barnett led the Blue Hose (7-6) in scoring, finishing with 14 points. Jonah Pierce added 11 points and six rebounds for Presbyterian. In addition, Samage Teel had eight points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
